technically yes, as it falls under the unatended macroing section. and they have done people in over it before (never more than a warning i believe though).
<br />

<br />
The gamepad trick would technically be considered a form of macro i believe. But, by its nature, it is not an unattended macro, sine you gotta pick your targets to shoot at activelym, and thus, it is safe. the game itself doesnthave support for gamepads or joysticks builtin. if you so wished, you could set up your gamepad/joystick programming software to fully emulate all your regular keyboard shortcuts and play the game almsot completely with the gamepad/joystick. is being a keyboard based game a "design feature" that is a part of the "game content"? i dont htink you can honestly say yes that. gamepad is no diferent from setting up your gamepad to use it to control the game instead of the keyboard.
<br />

<br />
yes, they originallyd esigned it to be one press, one arrow, but at that time, arrows were just a toy, and they were never meant to be serious. now they are. the 2 elements of game design just havent met each other in the middle yet (and since its very unlikely the bow as a main weapon thing is going away....) so we adapt and overcome, and rig a gamepad to save our fingers.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 12px; line-height: normal">----<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=433162" target="_blank" class="postlink">Daggerwolf Sleepytooth</a>
